721129f-a.text:
Liberty Street, north side, between Greenwich and
washington Streets, showing a 9 foot alley between No's 129 and 131 which according to the City Record appears to be ownerless. Its is 72 feet deep and of irregular witch, leading to the rear of buildings that face on the west side of Greenwich Street. At the northern extremity is the side of thne building in which John Thomas Smith lived and recently died in; No. 154 Greenwich Street.
August 1938
George D. Chinn
